Nigeria’s second game in the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations qualifying series, is an away fixture against Lesotho on Sunday. The Super Eagles began their quest to be at the tournament, with a 2-1 win over Benin Republic on Wednesday. Lesotho battled to a 1-1 draw with Sierra Leone in their opening game. Kick off is 5pm West African time. Nigeria XI vs Lesotho: Akpeyi; Awaziem, Aina, Ekong, Ajayi; Ndidi, Iwobi, Aribo; Simon, Chukwueze, Osimhen Sunday, November 17
First half: Masoabi Nkoto opened scoring for Lesotho, before goals from Iwobi and Chukwueze made it 2-1. Half time. Second half: Osimhen scores twice to make it 4-1, before an Awaziem own goal Full time: Nigeria have defeated Lesotho 4-2. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.